<p><i><b>Hard Candy</b></i> is a <a href="/wiki/2006" title="2006">2006</a> <a href="/wiki/Independent_film" title="Independent film">independent</a> <a href="/wiki/Psychological_thriller" title="Psychological thriller">psychological thriller</a> film focusing on a confrontation between a <a href="/wiki/Sexual_predator" title="Sexual predator">sexual predator</a> and a 14-year-old girl he attempts to ensnare.</p>
<p><i>Hard Candy</i> was directed by <a href="/wiki/David_Slade" title="David Slade">David Slade</a>, written by <a href="/wiki/Brian_Nelson_(screenwriter)" title="Brian Nelson (screenwriter)">Brian Nelson</a>, and stars <a href="/wiki/Patrick_Wilson_(actor)" title="Patrick Wilson (actor)">Patrick Wilson</a> and <a href="/wiki/Ellen_Page" title="Ellen Page">Ellen Page</a>, who rose to fame as the star of the 2007 academy award winning-film, <i>Juno.</i><sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2" title=""><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup> It was the first feature film for Slade, who previously had worked mostly in <a href="/wiki/Music_video" title="Music video">music videos</a>. The film inspired the music video for the <a href="/wiki/OOMPH!" title="OOMPH!" class="mw-redirect">OOMPH!</a> song "<a href="/wiki/Beim_ersten_Mal_tut%27s_immer_weh" title="Beim ersten Mal tut's immer weh">Beim ersten Mal tut's immer weh</a>"</p>
